[1] Case update
- Tue 27 Nov 2018. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., edited] https://mailchi.mp/sante.gouv.cd/ebola_kivu_27nov

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 26 Nov 2018:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 421, of which 374 are confirmed and 47 are probable. In total, there were 241 deaths (194 confirmed and 47 probable) and 125 people healed.
- 74 suspected cases under investigation.
- 2 new confirmed cases, including 1 in Kyondo and 1 in Kalunguta [North Kivu].
- 1 new death in Beni [North Kivu].
- 2 new people healed out of the ETC of Butembo [North Kivu].

News of the response
Vaccination
-----------
Since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 36 612 people were vaccinated, including 17 465 in Beni [North Kivu], 5017 in Katwa [North Kivu], 4544 in Mabalako [North Kivu], 2630 in Butembo [North Kivu], 1788 in Kalunguta [North Kivu], 1663 in Mandima [Ituri], 732 in Masereka [North Kivu], 521 in Oicha [North Kivu], 434 in Bunia [Ituri], 359 in Vuhovi [North Kivu], 355 in Tchomia [Ituri], 355 at Mutwanga [North Kivu], 241 at Kyondo [North Kivu], 240 at Komanda [Ituri], 234 at Musienene [North Kivu], and 34 at Alimbongo [North Kivu].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

